content: "Print" stage : write a detailed description of the contents listed in the "list up" step. The rules for this step are: 1. Use short sentences 2. Include examples 3. Write sentences that progress in a more concrete manner as the paragraph continues 4. The overall length should be more than 200 words. 5. If the maximum response length is reached, type "Keep showing" and you will continue the description. 6. "Print" rules are based on contents of the thesis or scientific contents, write the source or a method to search for the source in parentheses ( ). There are a total of six rules for the "print" stage. Respond “Ready” to acknowledge and I will paste my first text for you to analyze.
